---

<BaseLayout
  title="Kanha Birds 2026 - 300+ Species, Birdwatching Guide & Best Zones"
  description="Complete birdwatching guide for Kanha National Park. 300+ species including raptors, woodpeckers, flycatchers, and winter migrants. Best zones, seasons, and tips for birding."
  keywords="kanha birds, kanha birdwatching, kanha bird species, kanha raptors, kanha birds list"
  canonicalUrl="https://jungle-safari.github.io/kanha-tiger-guide/wildlife/birds/"
>
  <Header />

  <main class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 py-6">
    <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
      <div class="lg:col-span-2">

    <Breadcrumb items={breadcrumbs} />

    <h1>Kanha Birds 2026 — 300+ Species, Birdwatching Guide & Best Zones</h1>

        <TrustBar category="Travel Guide" readingTime={8} />

        <p class="text-lg italic text-gray-600 mb-6">Last updated: July 18, 2026</p>

    <Hero
      src="/images/Untitled-design-3-1.webp"
      alt="Birdlife at Kanha National Park - over 300 species of birds"
      caption="Kanha hosts over 300 bird species including raptors, woodpeckers, and winter migrants"
    />

    <section class="answer-block">
      <p>
        Kanha National Park hosts over <strong>300 recorded bird species</strong> across its four zones,
        making it one of central India's premier birdwatching destinations. The bird list includes resident
        species, winter migrants from Central Asia and the Himalayas, and local migrants. Iconic species
        include the <strong>Indian Peafowl</strong> (state bird of Madhya Pradesh), Crested Serpent Eagle,
        White-bellied Woodpecker, Indian Pitta (winter), Asian Paradise Flycatcher, and over 30 raptor
        species. The best time for birdwatching is <strong>November through February</strong> during winter
        migration. Sarhi Zone offers the quietest, most productive birding, while Kisli Zone's mature Sal
        forests harbor diverse forest species.
      </p>
    </section>

    <Backlink       title="Best Kanha Tiger Safari Packages 2026"
      description="Get the best Kanha tiger safari packages starting from ₹X,XXX per person. Wildmark Resort near Khatia Gate provides comfortable stays with safari permits, jeep, and guide included."
      anchorText="View Kanha Safari Package Deals"
      ctaText="Kanha Tiger Safari Booking"
      primaryUrl="https://kanhasafaristay.com/blog/wildlife-of-kanha-national-park-beyond-the-tiger/"
      primaryAnchor="Kanha Birds Wildlife Guide"
      secondaryUrl="https://kanhasafaristay.com/blog/best-time-to-visit-kanha-national-park-for-tiger-safari/"
      secondaryAnchor="Best Time for Kanha Birding"
      tertiaryUrl="https://kanhasafaristay.com/faq/"
      tertiaryAnchor="Kanha Birds FAQ"
    />

    <h2>Bird Diversity at Kanha</h2>

    <p>
      Kanha's 940 sq km landscape supports exceptional bird diversity through varied habitats — Sal forests,
      bamboo thickets, meadows, water bodies, and edge environments. The park's location on the central Indian
      plateau places it on major migration routes, attracting winter visitors from the Himalayas and Central Asia.
    </p>

    <h3>Habitat Types</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Dense Sal forests:</strong> Forest interior species, woodpeckers, owls</li>
      <li><strong>Bamboo thickets:</strong> Specialized bamboo species, warblers</li>
      <li><strong>Meadows (Dadars):</strong> Ground birds, partridges, pipits</li>
      <li><strong>Water bodies:</strong> Waders, ducks, kingfishers</li>
      <li><strong>Forest edges:</strong> Flycatchers, warblers, babblers</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Iconic Bird Species at Kanha</h2>

    <h3>Raptors (30+ species)</h3>
    <p>
      Kanha hosts an impressive raptor diversity with over 30 species recorded. Most commonly sighted:
    </p>

    <ul>
      <li><strong>Crested Serpent Eagle:</strong> Most commonly seen raptor; soars over forests and meadows</li>
      <li><strong>Changeable Hawk Eagle:</strong> Forest hunter; often perched mid-canopy</li>
      <li><strong>Black-shouldered Kite:</strong> Open habitat hunter; hovers over meadows</li>
      <li><strong>Shikra:</strong> Small accipiter; hunts in forest edges</li>
      <li><strong>Oriental Honey Buzzard:</strong> Migrant species; visible in winter</li>
      <li><strong>White-eyed Buzzard:</strong> Common winter visitor</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Woodpeckers (8+ species)</h3>
    <p>
      Kanha's mature forests support diverse woodpecker populations:
    </p>

    <ul>
      <li><strong>White-bellied Woodpecker:</strong> Large, distinctive, forest interior</li>
      <li><strong>Rufous Woodpecker:</strong> Bamboo specialist</li>
      <li><strong>Black-rumped Flameback:</strong> Common, widespread</li>
      <li><strong>Yellow-crowned Woodpecker:</strong> Smaller, forest edges</li>
      <li><strong>Brown-capped Pygmy Woodpecker:</strong> Tiny, often missed</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Flycatchers (15+ species)</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Asian Paradise Flycatcher:</strong> Spectacular long-tailed male, summer visitor</li>
      <li><strong>Verditer Flycatcher:</strong> Winter migrant, blue plumage</li>
      <li><strong>Tickell's Blue Flycatcher:</strong> Resident, forest streams</li>
      <li><strong>Red-breasted Flycatcher:</strong> Common winter visitor</li>
      <li><strong>White-browed Fantail:</strong> Year-round, very active</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Owls and Nightjars (12+ species)</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Indian Scops Owl:</strong> Small, common, nocturnal calls</li>
      <li><strong>Mottled Wood Owl:</strong> Forest species, often heard at dusk</li>
      <li><strong>Brown Fish Owl:</strong> Large, waterhole habitat</li>
      <li><strong>Jungle Owlet:</strong> Small, vocal, forest interior</li>
      <li><strong>Savanna Nightjar:</strong> Ground nester, evening activity</li>
    </ul>

    <Backlink       title="Birding Packages at Kanha"
      description="Wildmark Resort near Khatia Gate can arrange specialized birding-focused stays with expert naturalist guides and extended morning sessions in productive birding habitats."
      primaryUrl="https://kanhasafaristay.com/blog/wildlife-of-kanha-national-park-beyond-the-tiger/"
      primaryAnchor="Kanha Birds Wildlife Guide"
      secondaryUrl="https://kanhasafaristay.com/blog/best-time-to-visit-kanha-national-park-for-tiger-safari/"
      secondaryAnchor="Best Time for Kanha Birding"
      tertiaryUrl="https://kanhasafaristay.com/faq/"
      tertiaryAnchor="Kanha Birds FAQ"
